On 2018-11-11 20:06, Donald Tarallo wrote:
> Hi Cindy,
> 
> 1. KEEP GOING WITH THIS THEME. Pay attention to the focus. At times
> you loose the sharpness.
> Take 10 more. Select the best 10. Arrange them in some designed way.
> This should be linear (one after the other). They can touch or they
> could not touch, they can all be equal in size or some could be bigger
> than others. Some could be cropped and some could not be cropped.
> Trust your intuition and your eye to make a series that connects well
> as a series on a visual level. You seem to focus on two distinct
> elements; on nature and closeups of forms from human-made things.
> Refine this idea. We will print this on the same printer we made the
> hiking image with. So 13 inches high by as long as you need it to be.
> Montage this in one psd.
> 
> 2. FOR THE NEXT STUDY LETS TRY THIS. Lets follow through with the
> theme we proposed; _camera as pen_. Try to tell a story in 10 images.
> The story can be up to you, but I suggest something that includes
> human interaction. This study should utilize all of the past projects,
> depth of field, motion, and the techniques you learned from your
> chosen photographer. Write it out in words, then make it happen in
> images. It could also be closeups. It may be fun to write a short
> story first.
